                            <comment id="17032959" author="emilles" created="Sat, 8 Feb 2020 18:02:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;this.setProperty(&quot;value&quot;, &quot;def&quot;)&lt;/tt&gt; ends up running through &lt;tt&gt;BuilderSupport#doInvokeMethod&lt;/tt&gt;, which throws the missing method exception because it does not receive a Map or Closure as one of the arguments.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17033029" author="emilles" created="Sat, 8 Feb 2020 20:37:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;If you enable &quot;indy&quot;, this case succeeds.  So that is one workaround available to you before a new release carries a fix for the default dynamic path.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
